    {
      "id": "PopularPost231622",
      "post_content": "So...so versatile. Lets to the run down of all the myriad of ways to use this, okay?  \n1. Straight up casting. ![2](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=2&type=symbol)![Black](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=B&type=symbol) for a sorcery speedy -3/-3 is fair, if a touch inefficient nowadays.  \n2. Cycling. Nothing to see here.  \n3. Cycling with Madness. Basically an additional ![3](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=3&type=symbol) for instant speed and cantriping isn't too bad. (That's a word, right?)  \n4. Spellshaper fuel. Tacking on this effect to any spellshaper is a blast, as is most anything with madness.  \n5. Reaction to opponent's discard effect. Nothing is quite as insulting as breaking your fist when hitting an opponent. Again, this goes for anything with madness, so that's not too impressive, but still. Card advantage and whatnot.  \n  \nThat's about it. Five uses for one spell. Um...What other spell is quite this modular again? I can't think of many. There are a few, but at common? Not likely.",
      "posted_by": "DoragonShinzui",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost231622\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_post\">So...so versatile. Lets to the run down of all the myriad of ways to use this, okay?<br/>1. Straight up casting. <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"2\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=2&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Black\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=B&amp;type=symbol\"/> for a sorcery speedy -3/-3 is fair, if a touch inefficient nowadays.<br/>2. Cycling. Nothing to see here.<br/>3. Cycling with Madness. Basically an additional <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"3\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=3&amp;type=symbol\"/> for instant speed and cantriping isn't too bad. (That's a word, right?)<br/>4. Spellshaper fuel. Tacking on this effect to any spellshaper is a blast, as is most anything with madness.<br/>5. Reaction to opponent's discard effect. Nothing is quite as insulting as breaking your fist when hitting an opponent. Again, this goes for anything with madness, so that's not too impressive, but still. Card advantage and whatnot.<br/><br/>That's about it. Five uses for one spell. Um...What other spell is quite this modular again? I can't think of many. There are a few, but at common? Not likely.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '231622'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\"